The "Dynamic Tracking Link" (HTML)
The Goal: Create a clickable link in a search result that says "Track Package." It should dynamically change the URL based on whether the carrier is UPS or FedEx.

The Challenge: Combining string concatenation || with conditional CASE WHEN and HTML tags.

The Expected Logic:
CASE WHEN {shippingmethod} = 'UPS' 
THEN '<a href="https://www.ups.com/track?tracknum=' || {trackingnumbers} || '" target="_blank">Track UPS</a>'
WHEN {shippingmethod} = 'FedEx' 
THEN '<a href="https://www.fedex.com/track?tracknumbers=' || {trackingnumbers} || '" target="_blank">Track FedEx</a>'
ELSE 'No Tracking' END



